Combining two 'artificial, soft, cut' items reliably makes a 50-point item. The 'frame' tool can then boost these 50-point combined items even higher, sometimes to 70! Avoid using tools on 'hard' items as they often result in negative values. Also, be careful mixing 'natural' and 'artificial' features in complex combinations, as this can make items 'overcomplicated' and significantly reduce their value. Stick to cutting soft things and combining artificial soft cuts, then frame your best combo for a high score!

Be cautious applying scissors to items mixing soft and hard features, as this can also lead to negative scores.
